# SwiftFormat configuration — https://github.com/nicklockwood/SwiftFormat
#
# This project's style is enforced by SwiftFormat. SwiftLint (see .swiftlint.yml)
# handles semantic rules only; SwiftFormat owns all style/whitespace/brace rules.
#
# Run `script/format.sh` to auto-format, `script/lint.sh` to check without
# modifying files. CI runs `swiftformat --lint` as a strict gate.
#
# The options below are intentionally minimal: they describe the style the
# codebase already follows (4-space indent, K&R braces, no trailing whitespace)
# without imposing line wrapping (the project uses long lines for SwiftUI
# modifier chains and OSLog privacy-annotated interpolations).

--swift-version 6

# Files and directories to skip (build output, Xcode user state)
--exclude Apple/build,.build,Apple/PaxHistoriaApple.xcodeproj/xcuserdata,*.xcuserdata,Apple/PaxHistoriaApple.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace/xcuserdata

# Indentation: 4 spaces (matches existing code)
--indent 4

# K&R brace style (opening brace on same line) — matches existing code
--allman false

# Preserve file header comments (don't strip license/attribution blocks)
--header ignore

# Trim trailing whitespace on all lines
--trim-whitespace always

# Match existing trailing-comma usage (none on simple lists)
--trailing-commas never

# Disable line wrapping — the project intentionally uses long lines for
# SwiftUI chains and OSLog privacy annotations. Re-enable per-file if desired.
--disable wrap

# Preserve explicit `self.` — the project uses Swift 6 strict concurrency and
# requires explicit `self.` inside OSLog autoclosures and escaping closures.
# SwiftFormat's `redundantSelf` rule would strip these and break the build.
--disable redundantSelf
